SIMPLE: too
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Too
<hw>Too</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[The same word as
<ets>to</ets>, prep. See <er>To</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Over; more than enough; -- noting excess; <as>as, a
thing is <ex>too</ex> long, <ex>too</ex> short, or <ex>too</ex> wide;
<ex>too</ex> high; <ex>too</ex> many; <ex>too</ex> much</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His will, <qex>too</qex> strong to bend, <qex>too</qex> proud to
learn.</q> <rj><qau>Cowley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Likewise; also; in addition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An honest courtier, yet a patriot <qex>too</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let those eyes that view⟦br⟧
The daring crime, behold the vengeance <qex>too</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Too too</b></col>, <cd>a duplication used to signify
great excess.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O that this <qex>too too</qex> solid flesh would melt.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such is not Charles his <qex>too too</qex> active age.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Also; likewise. See <er>Also</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Took</ent>⟦br⟧
